    solution: `<strong>a)</strong>\n- $(x+3)^2 = x^2 + 6x + 9$\n- $(2x-1)^2 = 4x^2 - 4x + 1$\n- $(x+5)(x-5) = x^2 - 25$\n\n<strong>b)</strong>\n- $x^2 - 16 = \\mathbf{(x-4)(x+4)}$\n- $9x^2 - 6x + 1 = \\mathbf{(3x-1)^2}$\n\n<strong>c)</strong>\n- $101^2 = (100+1)^2 = 10\\,000 + 200 + 1 = \\mathbf{10\\,201}$\n- $99 \\times 101 = (100)^2 - 1^2 = \\mathbf{9\\,999}$`,
